N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 80.120 - Powers of commissioner

State Regulations

The commissioner, and any representative authorized by him, shall have the power to administer oaths, compel the attendance of witnesses and the production of books, papers and records and to take proof and testimony concerning all matters within the jurisdiction of the department. Notes
